msgid ""
"IPv6 may work out of the box in many cases. But in some cases or some "
"specific provider, you may need to tweak things manually to enable IPv6."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "With a VPS from OVH"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:11
msgid ""
"OVH gives one IPv4 address and one IPv6 address for VPS but by default, only "
"IPv4 is OK.  Please check [The OVH documentation](https://docs.ovh.com/gb/en/"
"vps/configuring-ipv6/)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configure the DNS server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:15
msgid ""
"Also check [the documentation for subdomains](/admin/tutorials/domains/"
"dns_subdomains)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configure the server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:19
msgid "On the OVH panel, you will copy 3 elements:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:23
msgid "the IPv6 address"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:23
msgid "the IPv6 gateway address"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:23
msgid ""
"the IPv6 prefix. On OVH's VPS SSD, prefixes are `/128` because you have only "
"*one* IPv6 address."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:26
msgid ""
"On your VPS, create a backup of the network configuration with : `cp /etc/"
"network/interfaces ~/interfaces` in home directory.  Then, you can edit the "
"configuration file (`/etc/network/interfaces`) with the following."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block (note)
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "In this example, it is assumed that your network interface is `eth0`. If it's different (check with `ip a`) you need to adapt the example below.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (text)
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:31
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"iface eth0 inet6 static\n"
"address <your IPv6 address>\n"
"netmask <your IPv6 prefix>\n"
"post-up /sbin/ip -6 route add <the IPv6 gateway> dev eth0\n"
"post-up /sbin/ip -6 route add default via <the IPv6 gateway> dev eth0\n"
"pre-down /sbin/ip -6 route del default via <the IPv6 gateway> dev eth0\n"
"pre-down /sbin/ip -6 route del <the IPv6 gateway> dev eth0\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:42
msgid ""
"Now, save the file and restart the network service with : `service "
"networking restart`. (TODO : ideally we should find a way to validate the "
"content of the configuration, otherwise it could fuck up the network stack "
"and get disconnected from the VPS ?)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:44
msgid "Check your configuration with these commands :"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:49
msgid "`ip a` to display network interfaces and addresses"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:49
msgid "`hostname -I` to display the system IP addresses"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:49
msgid ""
"try to ping an IPv6 server (for example you can use `ping6 ip6.yunohost.org`)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:49
msgid ""
"try to ping your server from your PC (assuming your PC has IPv6 enabled)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/50.troubleshooting/20.ipv6.mdx:50
msgid "If it's ok, it's ok !"
msgstr ""
